      "content": "i feel like that's just a vague answer lol. if you look at how it actually plays out in real life—like when people get cancelled or when certain views are just banned from being discussed—doesn't that lean more towards it being a negative force for censorship? it seems like the \"social justice\" part is just an excuse for it.",
